<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<ApexClass xmlns="http://soap.sforce.com/2006/04/metadata">
    <apiVersion>45.0</apiVersion>
    <status>Active</status>
    <userStory>As a Salesforce developer, I need to create an Apex class called DocumentVerificationClass with methods to verify documents, validate credit evaluation, and disburse funds.</userStory>
    <acceptanceCriteria>The documentverificationMethod method must take two input parameters (identityVerification and addressVerification) and return a success message if both are verified, an incomplete verification message if both are not verified, or a message indicating which is not verified if only one is not verified.The validatecreditevaluation method must take two input parameters (annualIncome and creditScore) and return a congratulatory message if annualIncome is equal to or greater than $30,000 and creditScore is 700 or higher, or a message indicating eligibility for a credit score with a moderate limit if annualIncome is equal to or greater than $20,000 and creditScore is 600 or higher, or a message indicating that the user is not eligible for a credit score if the criteria are not met.The disbursement method must take the disbursed amount and vehicle assessment value as input parameters and return a message indicating that the vehicle assessment passed and the disbursed amount if the disbursed amount is less than or equal to the vehicle assessment value, a message indicating that the vehicle assessment failed and the loan amount cannot exceed the vehicle value if the disbursed amount is greater than the vehicle assessment value, a message indicating successful disbursement if payment approval is granted, a message indicating invalid vendor information if the vendor information verification fails, a message indicating lack of funds if there are insufficient funds for disbursement, or a prompt for payment approval if payment approval is required and not granted.</acceptanceCriteria>
</ApexClass>